WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.000
Today we're exploring unit fractions on a number line.

00:08.000 --> 00:18.000
A unit fraction has 1 as its numerator - like 1/2, 1/3, or 1/4.

00:18.000 --> 00:28.000
Let's see how these special fractions fit between 0 and 1 on our number line.

00:28.000 --> 00:38.000
When we divide the space between 0 and 1 into equal parts, we can mark where each unit fraction belongs.

00:38.000 --> 00:48.000
Notice how 1/2 sits right in the middle, while 1/3 is closer to the beginning.

00:48.000 --> 00:58.000
And 1/4 is even closer to 0, because we're taking just 1 piece out of 4 equal pieces.

00:58.000 --> 01:08.000
The pattern is clear: the bigger the bottom number, the smaller the unit fraction becomes.

01:08.000 --> 01:20.000
Understanding this helps us place any unit fraction exactly where it belongs on our number line.

01:20.000 --> 01:25.000
Ready to try placing some unit fractions yourself?